In [530]:
fig, ax = plt.subplots(1, 1, figsize=(15, 4)) #  #plt.subplot() 

ax.bar(index_unst, man, width=0.55, color="teal",label='Male') #alpha=0.8, 
ax.bar(index_unst, -woman, width=0.55, color="salmon", label='Female') #alpha=0.8,

#  
for i in index_unst:
    ax.annotate(man[i], xy=(i,man[i]+100), ha='center', va='center')
    ax.annotate(woman[i], xy=(i,-woman[i]-100), ha='center', va='center')
    # % 
    ax.annotate(str(man_per[i]) + "%", xy=(i,man[i]/2), ha='center', va='center')

for i in index_unst[:-2]:
    ax.annotate(str(woman_per[i]) + "%", xy=(i,-woman[i]/2), ha='center', va='center')

#  
for s in ['top', 'left', 'right', 'bottom']:
    ax.spines[s].set_visible(False)
    
# 
legend = ax.legend(loc='upper right', title='Sex')

#  
fig.text(0.1, 0.95, "Age/Gender distribution", fontsize=20)

plt.show()

gc = df_3[df_3['Q2'] != 'Unlabeled']
gc = gc.groupby(['Q3'])['Q2'].value_counts().unstack().drop("Other")
gc['Sum'] = gc.sum(axis=1)
gc['per_Man'] = np.round(gc['Man']/gc['Sum'], 2)
gc['per_Woman'] = np.round(gc['Woman']/gc['Sum'], 2)
